05343nam a22009015i 9780674065475DE-B159720190708092533.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||190708s2012    mau    fo  d z      eng d  a97806740654757 a10.4159/harvard.97806740654752doi  a(DE-B1597)178213  a(OCoLC)794003566  a(OCoLC)840435577  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  amaucUS-MA 4aB430b.R45 2012eb 7aPHI0020002bisacsh04a171/.32231 aReeve, C. D. C., eauthor.10aAction, Contemplation, and Happiness :bAn Essay on Aristotle /cC. D. C. Reeve. 1aCambridge, MA : bHarvard University Press, c[2012] 4cÂ©2012  a1 online resource   atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00t Frontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tAbbreviations and Editions -- t1 The Transmission of Form -- t2 Truth, Action, and Soul -- t3 Theoretical Wisdom -- t4 Virtue of Character -- t5 Practical Wisdom -- t6 Immortalizing Beings -- t7 Happiness -- t8 The Happiest Life -- tIndex of Passages -- tGeneral Index0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe notion of practical wisdom is one of Aristotle's greatest inventions. It has inspired philosophers as diverse as Martin Heidegger, Hans-Georg Gadamer, Elizabeth Anscombe, Michael Thompson, and John McDowell. Now a leading scholar of ancient philosophy offers a challenge to received accounts of practical wisdom by situating it in the larger context of Aristotle's views on knowledge and reality. That happiness is the end pursued by practical wisdom is commonly agreed. What is disputed is whether happiness is to be found in the practical life of political action, in which we exhibit courage, temperance, and other virtues of character, or in the contemplative life, where theoretical wisdom is the essential virtue. C. D. C. Reeve argues that the dichotomy is bogus, that these lives are in fact parts of a single life, which is the best human one. In support of this view, he develops innovative accounts of many of the central notions in Aristotle's metaphysics, epistemology, and psychology, including matter and form, scientific knowledge, dialectic, educatedness, perception, understanding, political science, practical truth, deliberation, and deliberate choice. These accounts are based directly on freshly translated passages from many of Aristotle's writings. Action, Contemplation, and Happiness is an accessible essay not just on practical wisdom but on Aristotle's philosophy as a whole.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aEthics, Ancient. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2012z978311029405708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2012z9783110294040oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674065475423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674065475.jpg  a978-3-11-029405-7  E-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2012b2012  a978-3-11-037488-9  HUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014  a978-3-11-037491-9  HUP eBook Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-044220-5  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2005-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-045951-7  H